<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-800-880  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 800 880.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC-Computing  Nov 1989 v2 n11 p231(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Douglas Cobb on spreadsheets. (Pro Tips)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cobb, Douglas.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Product:   Lotus 1-2-3 (Spreadsheet software) (usage).andO;Topic:     SpreadsheetsTutorial.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Douglas Cobb on SpreadsheetsandM;You're working in large 1-2-3 worksheet that takes several seconds torecalculate; you make one change and you want to see how it affects anothercell.andP;  How can you recalculate that cell without recalculating the wholeworksheet?andM;Move the cursor to the cell you want to recalculate, press Edit (F2), andpress Enter.andP;  The cell will now display its new value.andM;Now suppose you need to recalculate a few cells instead of just one or two.andO;Use the Copy command.andP;  Move the cursor to the first cell in the range youwant to recalculate, press / and then C for Copy, select the range of cellsyou want to recalculate as the From range, and press Enter to lock in yourselection.andP;  At this point, 1-2-3 will prompt you for the To range.andP;  Withoutmoving the cursor, just press Enter.andP;  When you do this, 1-2-3 will &quot;copy&quot;each entry in the range you selected back onto itself and recalculate eachformula in the process.andM;Beware.andP;  None of the formulas that refer to those cells will be updated untilyou recalculate them individually or recalculate the entire worksheet.andP;  Also,the Copy trick recalculates from left to right and from top to bottom in therange you select.andP;  References in the range that depend on values in cells tothe right or below them will not be recalculated properly.andM;Douglas Cobb, president of the Cobb Group, a Louisville, Kentucky, consultingcompany, is coauthor of Using 1-2-3 (Que Corporation).andO;</TEXT></DOC>